<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="45" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="45">
This species has records from Islay (
<geoCoordinate direction="south" orientation="latitude" precision="925" value="-17.05">17°03'S</geoCoordinate>
; 
<geoCoordinate direction="west" orientation="longitude" precision="925" value="-72.1">72°06'W</geoCoordinate>
), Peru to Chanavayita cove, 54 km south of Iquique, Chile (
<geoCoordinate direction="south" orientation="latitude" precision="925" value="-20.7">20°42'S</geoCoordinate>
; 
<geoCoordinate direction="west" orientation="longitude" precision="925" value="-70.15">70°09'W</geoCoordinate>
), with records also in the 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Galápagos">Galapagos</normalizedToken>
Islands (
<geoCoordinate direction="north" orientation="latitude" precision="925" value="1.6666667">01°40'N</geoCoordinate>
; 92°01 W), Ecuador (
<bibRefCitation author="Aguilera, MA" journalOrPublisher="Investigaciones Marinas" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" pagination="207 - 210" title="Consideraciones taxonomicas de Callistochitonpulchellus (Gray, 1828) (Mollusca, Placophora) en Iquique, norte de Chile." volume="33" year="2005 a">Aguilera 2005a</bibRefCitation>
). The present record (at 27°S) is now the southernmost record for this species.
</paragraph>
